<rss version="2.0" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:ss="http://contenthub.aol.com/slideshow/"><channel><title><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></title><link/> https://www.engadget.com/ <description><![CDATA[Engadget is a web magazine with obsessive daily coverage of everything new in gadgets and consumer electronics]]></description><language> en-US</language><copyright>版权所有雅虎 2024</copyright><pubDate> Fri, 07 Jun 2024 13:48:40 +0000</pubDate><generator>雅虎 http://yahoo.com </generator><item><title><![CDATA[Apple's AI push will reportedly be called Apple Intelligence, of course]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>就在苹果全球开发者大会 (WWDC 2024) 开幕前几天， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-06-07/apple-wwdc-2024-what-to-expect-ai-ipados-18-macos-15-siri-updates-more?sref=10lNAhZ9"><em>彭博社的马克·古尔曼 (Mark Gurman)</em></a>公布了他最后一轮的剧透细节。最大的收获是：苹果将其传闻已久的人工智能游戏称为“Apple Intelligence”。 （让苹果公司找到某种方法来重新定义“人工智能”一词。）不要指望该公司会像竞争对手那样倾向于生成人工智能功能。古尔曼表示，苹果的人工智能功能将专注于具有“广泛吸引力”的功能——我认为这比按需创建迷幻图像更实用。</p><p> Apple Intelligence 将由该公司的技术<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-has-reportedly-resumed-talks-with-openai-to-build-a-chatbot-for-the-iphone-002302644.html">以及 OpenAI 的</a>技术组合提供支持。<em>彭博社</em>还指出，人工智能功能将主要是选择性加入的，我们可以预期苹果会宣传其安全功能，因为它也将依赖于设备上和云连接的组合。此前，苹果曾吹嘘 iPhone 的设备安全性比 Android 等竞争对手更有效。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>正如<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-is-reportedly-overhauling-siri-with-ai-for-improved-voice-controls-120033411.html">之前的传闻</a>，Gurman 表示 Siri 将能够使用 Apple Intelligence 更直接地控制应用程序。您可以告诉助手以某种方式总结文章或编辑照片。值得注意的是，据报道，苹果计划向第三方开放此功能，并允许您将多个命令串在一起 - 但这些功能要到明年才能提供。</p><p>至于其他功能，听起来苹果正在尽可能地融入人工智能。据报道，您将能够创建可以使用文本字符串进行自定义的人工智能表情符号，并且您可以期望在语音备忘录中看到人工智能转录以及更多人工智能照片编辑功能。 </p><div id="8db9cab62883478cb614c6d914e6e837"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/AogWbUmC4ww?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div></div><p></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/apples-ai-push-will-reportedly-be- Called-apple-intelligence-of-course-134840050.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apples-ai-push-will-reportedly-be-called-apple-intelligence-of-course-134840050.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 46653ddd-e5ac-4556-8bdc-a128ea7305df </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Devindra Hardawar]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 07 Jun 2024 13:48:41 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1717768122</ingested><modified> 2024-06-07T13:48:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Devindra Hardawar]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2F5362d4a0-24d3-11ef-b7fc-a40afd350ca8&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=63cfb02d58eafcb582a7896e93bfa33ec4973307" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-06%2F5362d4a0-24d3-11ef-b7fc-a40afd350ca8&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=8061dfab82bc194a41bfc388acb7a772b715705f" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Cherlynn Low/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[iPhone 15 Pro]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[iPhone 15 Pro]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Whistleblower claims Amazon violated UK sanctions by selling facial recognition tech to Russia]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>据<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.ft.com/content/f28377a1-432b-4f29-8544-e5ec7ac1cab9"><em>英国《金融时报》</em></a>报道，一名前雇员指责亚马逊在入侵乌克兰后向莫斯科出售面部识别技术，违反了英国制裁。</p><p>文章称，查尔斯·福雷斯特 (Charles Forrest) 声称，他在 2022 年 11 月至 2023 年 5 月期间指控亚马逊在一系列问题上存在不当行为后，于 2023 年被不公平地解雇。作为本周听证会的一部分，这些指控已提交给伦敦就业法庭。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Forrest 表示，亚马逊与俄罗斯公司<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.reuters.com/business/media-telecom/russias-mts-acquire-biometrics-firm-visionlabs-95-million-2021-12-13/">VisionLabs</a>达成了一项协议，提供其<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-01-25-amazon-rekognition-facial-analysis-gender-race-bias-mit.html">Rekognition</a>面部识别技术。根据法庭文件，该公司“通过一家看似位于荷兰的空壳公司”做到了这一点。他还指责该公司违反了乔治·弗洛伊德被谋杀后<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/silicon-valley-technology-race-reckoning-163023023.html">实施的</a>禁止警方使用面部识别技术的自我暂停令。</p><p>亚马逊否认了这些指控。一位发言人告诉<em>英国《金融时报》</em> ：“我们认为这些说法缺乏依据，并期待通过法律程序证明这一点。” “根据现有证据和计费记录，AWS 并未向 VisionLabs 出售 Amazon Rekognition 服务。”</p><p>亚马逊称，福雷斯特因拒绝按照合同规定的时间工作、未回复电子邮件或参加会议而因“严重不当行为”而被解雇。它否认福雷斯特做出了使他有权受到举报人保护的各种披露。</p><p>亚马逊似乎承认它违反了警方使用面部识别技术的禁令，同时补充说它没有违反任何法律。 “自我实施的暂停并不构成法律义务，”它说。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/whistleblower-claims-amazon-violated-uk-sanctions-by- sell-facial-recognition-tech-to-Russia-125001230.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/whistleblower-claims-amazon-violated-uk-sanctions-by-selling-facial-recognition-tech-to-russia-125001230.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 50714e4b-9283-4a66-861b-d1a761484779 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Steve Dent]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 07 Jun 2024 12:50:01 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1717764602</ingested><modified> 2024-06-07T12:50:11+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="753" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-05%2F6d4ac5f0-12a7-11ef-bed7-ca50de79f896&amp;resize=1400%2C753&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=3fcdf137933d5e13369d12e1e3505587414a0d5f" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="753" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-05%2F6d4ac5f0-12a7-11ef-bed7-ca50de79f896&amp;resize=1400%2C753&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=e506ec6e77cd6035955c378da24f4094292d30f2" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Jacob Wackerhausen via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Face recognition, man in street and identity with biometric, surveillance and code for technology innovation in city. Network, security and future, IT overlay with info and frame, privacy and UI]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Face recognition, man in street and identity with biometric, surveillance and code for technology innovation in city. Network, security and future, ai overlay with info and frame, privacy and UI]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Blackmagic's DaVinci Resolve 19 arrives for Qualcomm Snapdragon X Elite PCs]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>运行高通最新<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-snapdragon-x-elite-is-qualcomms-most-powerful-chip-to-date-190004830.html">Snapdragon X Elite</a>的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/here-are-all-of-the-just-announced-copilot-pcs-with-snapdragon-x-chips-184825090.html">Windows PC 的</a>性能尤其是效率足以让英特尔感到害怕，因此对内容创作者具有强大的吸引力。目前的问题是缺乏应用程序，但 Blackmagic Design 刚刚宣布其流行的（免费的） <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/blackmagics-davinci-resolve-19-arrives-with-ai-powered-motion-tracking-and-color-grading-090013746.html">DaVinci Resolve 19</a> （beta 3）视频编辑和效果软件现在支持运行新芯片的 Windows 机器。</p><p> Blackmagic Design 在一份新闻稿中写道：“DaVinci Resolve 19 beta 3 现在支持高通用于 Windows 的全新一体式 CPU、NPU 和 GPU 处理器 Snapdragon X Elite。” “DaVinci Resolve 经过微调，优化了达芬奇神经人工智能引擎的性能，NPU 加速使客户的 AI 工具（例如 Magic Mask）性能提高了 4.7 倍，并且使用这款新处理器的计算机上的智能重构性能提高了 2 倍。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Intel PC 和 Mac 上的所有 DaVinci Resolve 19 工具也都在 Qualcomm 平台上。其中包括“ColorSlice”色彩校正工具、Ultra NR 降噪、用于运动跟踪和稳定的 Intellitrack AI、音频“闪避”等。由于其中许多都是由人工智能驱动的，用户应该受益于 Snapdragon X Elite 的神经引擎 (NPU)，它击败了几乎所有笔记本电脑处理器。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-06/c441ea80-24a6-11ef-a6f7-0b56d26c9a45" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-06/c441ea80-24a6-11ef-a6f7-0b56d26c9a45" style="height:576px;width:960px;" alt="Qualcomm X Elite 笔记本电脑上的 Blackmagic Design DaVinci Resolve 19 beta 3" data-uuid="96584847-def5-38f8-895f-a705ab2a2c07"><figcaption>配备 Snapdragon X Elite 芯片的 Yoga Slim 7x 14 英寸笔记本电脑仅比 13 英寸 MacBook Air 重十分之一磅。</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">恩杰特</div></figure><p>Snapdragon X Elite还拥有出色的多线程CPU性能， <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.notebookcheck.net/Snapdragon-X-Elite-vs-Intel-Core-Ultra-and-Apple-M3-Qualcomm-s-SoC-reportedly-excels-in-efficiency-and-outperforms-Meteor-Lake.822152.0.html">超越了</a>许多英特尔芯片和苹果的M3。 VPU（视频处理单元）提供 AV1、VP9、HEVC (H.265) 和 H.264 编码和解码（最高 10 位），因此用户应该能够使用大多数本机相机格式并为 YouTube 和其他平台也很快。</p><p>不过，图形性能是一个弱点，其性能仅与英特尔 Core Ultra 7 相当，远低于大多数专用 GPU。与此同时，Apple M3 GPU（MacBook Air 上）以 31% 的优势击败了它。这意味着依赖 GPU 的 DaVinci Resolve 效果、编码等可能比 Wintel 和 MacBook M3 机器慢。</p><p>尽管如此，对于那些希望拥有一款能够与苹果笔记本电脑相媲美的轻型公路机器的内容创作者来说，这仍然是个好消息。适用于 Windows on Arm 和 Snapdragon X Elite 的 DaVinci Resolve 19 公共测试版 3 现已<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.blackmagicdesign.com/products/davinciresolve/whatsnew">可从 Blackmagic Design 网站下载</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/blackmagics-davinci-resolve-19-arrives-for-qualcomm-snapdragon-x-elite-pcs-123042761.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/blackmagics-davinci-resolve-19-arrives-for-qualcomm-snapdragon-x-elite-pcs-123042761.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5ac766b1-e936-48e9-b28d-775942b5f87c </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Steve Dent]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 07 Jun 2024 12:30:42 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1717749413</ingested><modified> 2024-06-07T08:37:04+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category>